dc_title_s: Poland 1:100,000. Tuchola, sheet L-12. A.M.S. M651 (G.S.G.S. 4416)
dc_description_s: AMS 2. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4416. Alternate title: Tuchola Poland. Polyconic projection. Russian belt 4 and Nord de guerre zone grids. Relief shown by 10 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. With a glossary. Compiled from Poland 1:100,000, Military Geographic Institute, Sheets 34-25, 1936; 34-26, 1933; 35-25, 1938; 35-26, 1934; Germany, 1:25,000, German General Staff, 1873-1933; Germany 1:100,000, German General Staff, Sheet 41, 1936. Road classification in Poland based on British intelligence reports, 1943.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
